						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab built into the wall in the backyard of the Taluk Office.</hi></p>						

						<p>Chālukya-Pratapāchakravarti (Jagadēkamalla II)—(Date lost).</p>						

						<p>This damaged record, in characters of about the <hi rend="bold">12th century A.D.,</hi> refers to the Chālukya king with the title <hi rend="italic">Pratāpachakravarti</hi> but his name is lost. He was probably Jagadēkamalladēva II who had this title. The inscription seems to record gifts of several <hi rend="italic">vṛittis</hi> of land to the individuals mentioned as also to some temples. All details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
